and apologize for that.

00:01:37.697 --> 00:01:39.966 line:95%,end
I don't feel that where my feelings
were coming from

00:01:40.033 --> 00:01:42.569 line:95%,end
or wrong based on things
that had happened to me

00:01:42.635 --> 00:01:45.772 line:95%,end
and Chloe for the last year,
two years, three years.

00:01:45.839 --> 00:01:47.574 line:95%,end
If you weren't happy
with the education,

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:48.675 line:95%,end
you should have left
after the first month.

00:01:48.741 --> 00:01:49.576 line:95%,end
I should have left.

00:01:49.642 --> 00:01:51.478 line:95%,end
Chloe would not be
a national title winner.

00:01:51.544 --> 00:01:52.912 line:95%,end
She would be nothing.

00:01:52.979 --> 00:01:55.849 line:95%,end
You're dumb for letting people
walk out of your studio left and right.

00:01:55.915 --> 00:01:59.419 line:95%,end
I was trying to be an adult
and be a bigger person,

00:01:59.486 --> 00:02:00.787 line:95%,end
and she just wasn't having it.

00:02:02.856 --> 00:02:05.225 line:95%,end
White trash.

00:02:05.291 --> 00:02:09.062 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>The contract Abby gave me</i>
<i>has incredible stipulations in it,</i>

00:02:09.129 --> 00:02:11.598 line:95%,end
<i>things like I'm not to walk into the den,</i>

00:02:11.664 --> 00:02:13.666 line:95%,end
<i>I'm not allowed to walk</i>
<i>into the dressing room,</i>

00:02:13.733 --> 00:02:15.902 line:95%,end
<i>that I agree</i>
<i>that I'm in the wrong.</i>

00:02:15.969 --> 00:02:17.637 line:95%,end
It's important
that Chloe stay at this studio

00:02:17.704 --> 00:02:19.772 line:95%,end
because she's a title holder.

00:02:19.839 --> 00:02:22.509 line:95%,end
<i>If we leave,</i>
<i>she loses her titles.</i>

00:02:22.575 --> 00:02:25.712 line:95%,end
You know,
do I sell my soul for a crown?

00:02:25.778 --> 00:02:28.848 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:02:28.915 --> 00:02:30.717 line:5%,start
ABBY: Girls, let's go!

00:02:30.783 --> 00:02:31.918 line:5%,start
Come on, ladies!

00:02:31.985 --> 00:02:33.286 line:95%,end
Come on, girls. Let's go!

00:02:33.353 --> 00:02:34.320 line:95%,end
Get in here!

00:02:34.387 --> 00:02:36.623 line:95%,end
First, I want to talk
about this past weekend.

00:02:36.689 --> 00:02:39.526 line:95%,end
I am very disappointed.

00:02:39.592 --> 00:02:42.896 line:95%,end
Every single one of you
could have done better on your solo.

00:02:42.962 --> 00:02:45.431 line:95%,end
Moving on,
I want to forget about last weekend.

00:02:45.498 --> 00:02:47.167 line:95%,end
What's going to happen
this weekend?

00:02:47.233 --> 00:02:49.269 line:95%,end
It's the ALDC Showcase.

00:02:49.335 --> 00:02:50.803 line:95%,end
Thank you. Yes.

00:02:50.870 --> 00:02:54.107 line:95%,end
<i>The annual Abby Lee</i>
<i>Dance Company Showcase</i>

00:02:54.174 --> 00:02:56.309 line:95%,end
<i>is an event that we do</i>

00:02:56.376 --> 00:02:59.646 line:95%,end
<i>to showcase</i>
<i>all of our competition numbers.</i>

00:02:59.712 --> 00:03:02.248 line:5%,start
This is when
their families, their friends,

00:03:02.315 --> 00:03:07.420 line:5%,start
all of the people
that really don't understand what they do,

00:03:07.487 --> 00:03:09.322 line:95%,end
get to come and see the end result.

00:03:09.389 --> 00:03:11.024 line:95%,end
<i>And at the Showcase</i>

00:03:11.090 --> 00:03:14.360 line:95%,end
<i>I watch every solo</i>
<i>and every group number.</i>

00:03:14.427 --> 00:03:16.396 line:95%,end
Then I make a decision
on what's going to go

00:03:16.462 --> 00:03:19.265 line:95%,end
to the next regionals
and onto nationals.

00:03:19.332 --> 00:03:22.235 line:5%,start
We're doing the new number,
"Sugar Daddies," at the showcase.

00:03:22.302 --> 00:03:26.139 line:95%,end
Maddie, you won the overall
high score at the competition. Boom.

00:03:26.206 --> 00:03:29.309 line:95%,end
Nia, forgot the "Solo Cup" dancing,
made it up, went on,

00:03:29.375 --> 00:03:30.510 line:95%,end
finished with the music.

00:03:30.577 --> 00:03:33.279 line:95%,end
HOLLY: <i>Nia was assigned</i>
<i>a little bit higher in the pyramid.</i>

00:03:33.346 --> 00:03:35.215 line:95%,end
I think Nia was very excited about that.

00:03:35.281 --> 00:03:37.050 line:95%,end
Chloe did a great job.

00:03:37.116 --> 00:03:39.152 line:95%,end
There were some other situations.

00:03:39.219 --> 00:03:40.153 line:95%,end
You're here.

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:41.888 line:95%,end
I want to see
that attitude improve on stage.

00:03:41.955 --> 00:03:43.189 line:95%,end
Yes?

00:03:43.256 --> 00:03:45.058 line:95%,end
You never know
who's watching you.

00:03:45.124 --> 00:03:47.560 line:95%,end
I honestly wasn't surprised
by the pyramid this week.

00:03:47.627 --> 00:03:51.264 line:95%,end
I knew Abby was going to punish Chloe
because of my behavior.


00:03:51.331 --> 00:03:54.734 line:95%,end
All right. I have a few surprises
during the showcase.

00:03:54.801 --> 00:03:57.303 line:95%,end
I don't want to pressure you,
but in the audience

00:03:57.370 --> 00:04:00.340 line:95%,end
at the showcase
it's going to be an agent

00:04:00.406 --> 00:04:04.310 line:95%,end
coming to seek new talent
and looking for new clients to sign.

00:04:04.377 --> 00:04:05.345 line:95%,end
Yes.

00:04:05.411 --> 00:04:07.914 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:04:07.981 --> 00:04:10.383 line:95%,end
When Abby said
that there was a Broadway talent agent

00:04:10.450 --> 00:04:12.885 line:95%,end
coming to the showcase,
my heart just stopped.

00:04:12.952 --> 00:04:14.254 line:95%,end
I mean, this is huge.

00:04:14.320 --> 00:04:18.291 line:95%,end
ABBY: Moms,
you are going to be performing

00:04:18.358 --> 00:04:19.792 line:95%,end
in the show, as well.

00:04:20.927 --> 00:04:22.929 line:95%,end
(cheering)

00:04:24.664 --> 00:04:27.533 line:95%,end
ABBY: Oh, Cathy,
you're going to be the choreographer.

00:04:28.768 --> 00:04:31.304 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:04:31.371 --> 00:04:32.905 line:95%,end
CATHY: You guys are in for trouble.

00:04:32.972 --> 00:04:34.907 line:95%,end
ABBY: Nationals are getting closer
and closer.

00:04:34.974 --> 00:04:38.077 line:95%,end
With every competition
you get better and you get stronger.

00:04:38.144 --> 00:04:41.814 line:95%,end
So this showcase is going to be
a nice chance to entertain

00:04:41.881 --> 00:04:44.884 line:95%,end
rather than compete,
but it all is leading up to nationals.

00:04:44.951 --> 00:04:46.052 line:95%,end
Because we want to do what?

00:04:46.119 --> 00:04:47.253 line:95%,end
Win!

00:04:47.320 --> 00:04:48.588 line:95%,end
You got it. All right.

00:04:48.655 --> 00:04:50.723 line:95%,end
I think Abby lays in bed
at night and thinks up this stuff.

00:04:50.790 --> 00:04:54.394 line:95%,end
We're going to be on stage
like the hippos in "Fantasia."

00:04:54.460 --> 00:04:55.962 line:95%,end
Go ahead.
You're dismissed.

00:04:56.029 --> 00:04:58.464 line:95%,end
Guys, up with "Sugar Daddies."

00:04:58.531 --> 00:05:00.700 line:95%,end
All right, let's go.
Okay, okay, you're like mosquitoes.

00:05:00.767 --> 00:05:03.536 line:5%,start
Get away. Get away. Get away.

00:05:03.603 --> 00:05:06.205 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:05:06.272 --> 00:05:07.240 line:5%,start
ABBY: Come on, girls.

00:05:08.675 --> 00:05:11.044 line:95%,end
Do something with your face. Come on!

00:05:11.110 --> 00:05:15.748 line:95%,end
"Sugar Daddies" is a pop jazz routine
and they use props.

00:05:15.815 --> 00:05:18.251 line:95%,end
<i>They're rectangular</i>
<i>in shape and they're--</i>

00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:19.218 line:95%,end
they're big.

00:05:19.285 --> 00:05:21.721 line:95%,end
<i>It's just kind of a nightmare.</i>

00:05:21.788 --> 00:05:25.191 line:95%,end
Girls, can I see
some emotional execution?

00:05:28.628 --> 00:05:30.730 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>After the pyramid,</i>
<i>we're sitting upstairs</i>

00:05:30.797 --> 00:05:31.864 line:95%,end
<i>in the viewing room.</i>

00:05:31.931 --> 00:05:34.434 line:95%,end
<i>And it's very awkward</i>
<i>and uncomfortable.</i>

00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:36.169 line:95%,end
Let's go in the hallway!

00:05:36.235 --> 00:05:37.570 line:95%,end
-I'm not going anywhere.
-ABBY: The children just won.

00:05:37.637 --> 00:05:39.372 line:95%,end
-My daughter's happy.
-CHRISTI: Let's go in the hallway.

00:05:39.439 --> 00:05:41.174 line:95%,end
Do you want to talk
about all the things

00:05:41.240 --> 00:05:43.042 line:95%,end
that need to be talked about?

00:05:43.109 --> 00:05:45.445 line:95%,end
CATHY: <i>Christi,</i>
<i>I think that she's a beast.</i>

00:05:45.511 --> 00:05:49.215 line:95%,end
<i>She is extremely jealous of Maddie.</i>

00:05:49.282 --> 00:05:52.218 line:5%,start
And Melissa was definitely
a victim, at that point.

00:05:52.285 --> 00:05:53.820 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I have had
some time to reflect,

00:05:53.886 --> 00:05:57.590 line:95%,end
and I just wanted to apologize
to you three and Holly, as well.

00:05:57.657 --> 00:06:00.126 line:95%,end
It just wasn't my finest moment as a--

00:06:00.193 --> 00:06:02.195 line:95%,end
an adult, as a person or as a parent.

00:06:02.261 --> 00:06:04.931 line:95%,end
You know, I hope
that we all can move past this.

00:06:04.997 --> 00:06:06.466 line:95%,end
I hope you won't hold it against me.

00:06:06.532 --> 00:06:07.633 line:95%,end
I made a mistake.

00:06:07.700 --> 00:06:10.903 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>As far as the fight goes</i>
<i>with Abby and Christi, I'm neutral.</i>

00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:13.706 line:5%,start
I see things Christi agrees with,
and same with Abby.

00:06:13.773 --> 00:06:16.709 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Well, I just want
to apologize to everybody for--

00:06:16.776 --> 00:06:18.478 line:95%,end
-for that. Because...
-Me, too.

00:06:19.645 --> 00:06:21.214 line:95%,end
It was just awful.

00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:22.815 line:95%,end
I don't even want to talk about it.

00:06:22.882 --> 00:06:24.484 line:95%,end
I just want to put it behind us.

00:06:24.550 --> 00:06:28.621 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>The thing with Melissa</i>
<i>is she doesn't like confrontation.</i>

00:06:28.688 --> 00:06:31.424 line:95%,end
So when you finally confront her,
you know, oh, no.

00:06:31.491 --> 00:06:33.493 line:95%,end
Everything's fine. Let's move on.
Everything's great.

00:06:33.559 --> 00:06:35.728 line:95%,end
<i>So we'll put on that nice front.</i>

00:06:35.795 --> 00:06:38.498 line:95%,end
<i>And, you know, underneath I think</i>
<i>all those emotions are still there.</i>

00:06:38.564 --> 00:06:41.901 line:95%,end
We have a long history,
and I absolutely think

00:06:41.968 --> 00:06:43.469 line:95%,end
Abby and Melissa
owe me an apology.

00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:45.838 line:95%,end
I'm the one who's apologizing.
But, you know what?

00:06:45.905 --> 00:06:47.407 line:95%,end
They were just as wrong as I was.

00:06:47.473 --> 00:06:50.576 line:95%,end
I think we just need to move on
and forget about it.

00:06:52.879 --> 00:06:54.013 line:95%,end
KELLY: I think we should go down

00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:55.381 line:95%,end
and see how much longer
they're going to be.

00:06:55.448 --> 00:06:56.482 line:95%,end
Okay.

00:06:58.317 --> 00:07:00.453 line:95%,end
ABBY: Back leg is not high enough!

00:07:03.656 --> 00:07:05.658 line:95%,end
Hold it, hold it, hold it.

00:07:11.364 --> 00:07:13.499 line:95%,end
(jazz music playing)

00:07:16.135 --> 00:07:18.438 line:95%,end
CATHY: <i>I was really happy</i>
<i>that Abby chose me</i>

00:07:18.504 --> 00:07:20.106 line:95%,end
to choreograph a mom's dance.

00:07:21.674 --> 00:07:25.611 line:95%,end
<i>My vision is that I give them</i>
<i>very simple choreography</i>

00:07:25.678 --> 00:07:27.980 line:95%,end
<i>that is going</i>
<i>to make them look good.</i>

00:07:28.047 --> 00:07:30.349 line:95%,end
Because I'm sure
that all of them have two left feet.

00:07:31.684 --> 00:07:33.019 line:95%,end
-Hello.
-Oh!

00:07:33.085 --> 00:07:35.855 line:95%,end
-Hi!
-Hello. Are you guys ready?

00:07:35.922 --> 00:07:37.557 line:95%,end
I don't know
if we'll ever be ready.

00:07:37.623 --> 00:07:39.659 line:95%,end
<i>I was one of Abby's students</i>
<i>years ago,</i>

00:07:39.725 --> 00:07:42.895 line:95%,end
so it's weird for me to be in the studio
as a dancer again,


00:07:42.962 --> 00:07:44.497 line:95%,end
and not as a dance mom.

00:07:44.564 --> 00:07:46.199 line:95%,end
And one and two,
sit, three, four,

00:07:46.265 --> 00:07:47.600 line:95%,end
go five, go six, go seven...

00:07:47.667 --> 00:07:50.236 line:95%,end
-(laughter)
-This is so embarrassing!

00:07:50.303 --> 00:07:53.873 line:95%,end
And a one, two, three,
four, five, six, seven, eight.

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:55.741 line:95%,end
-Hi, Holly.
-Hi, birthday girl!

00:07:55.808 --> 00:07:57.543 line:95%,end
CATHY: You look like you're ready
to dance.

00:07:57.610 --> 00:08:00.413 line:95%,end
-We're still missing Christi, obviously.
-It's hot in here.

00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:03.883 line:95%,end
CATHY: We had a rehearsal call time
that I had scheduled.

00:08:03.950 --> 00:08:05.918 line:95%,end
<i>Christi, however, was not there.</i>

00:08:05.985 --> 00:08:07.720 line:95%,end
And it seems
like at every turn

00:08:07.787 --> 00:08:09.655 line:95%,end
there there's a dramatic issue with her.

00:08:09.722 --> 00:08:12.191 line:95%,end
Drop step, ball change.

00:08:14.994 --> 00:08:16.596 line:95%,end
Gosh, I'm so glad
that you decided

00:08:16.662 --> 00:08:18.531 line:95%,end
to finally grace us with your presence.

00:08:20.166 --> 00:08:22.034 line:95%,end
<i>Christi came in very late.</i>

00:08:22.101 --> 00:08:24.203 line:95%,end
We had very little time
to prepare for this,

00:08:24.270 --> 00:08:26.706 line:95%,end
<i>and I expect you</i>
<i>to be on time to get the job done.</i>

00:08:26.772 --> 00:08:28.508 line:95%,end
All right.
So you watch what we're doing,

00:08:28.574 --> 00:08:30.142 line:95%,end
Christi, and try to take notes.

00:08:30.209 --> 00:08:33.846 line:95%,end
One and two, ball change, Lindy.

00:08:33.913 --> 00:08:35.214 line:95%,end
CHRISTI:
I'm not interested in dancing.

00:08:35.281 --> 00:08:36.482 line:95%,end
My ship has sailed.

00:08:36.549 --> 00:08:37.850 line:95%,end
I don't want to be on stage.

00:08:37.917 --> 00:08:40.586 line:95%,end
<i>And not only do I have</i>
<i>to perform this dance</i>

00:08:40.653 --> 00:08:42.321 line:95%,end
<i>that I really don't want to do,</i>

00:08:42.388 --> 00:08:46.325 line:95%,end
but then I have to let Cathy
be in charge of me.

00:08:46.392 --> 00:08:48.628 line:95%,end
<i>I mean, I have to do it</i>
<i>or Abby's going to punish Chloe,</i>

00:08:48.694 --> 00:08:51.197 line:95%,end
<i>whether it be for me</i>
